blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"According to #98 `and` / `or` should be supported, but they are not fully working.\r\n\r\nConsider this: https://psalm.dev/r/196ea5bbc8\r\n\r\nTwo issues are raised, even if the code works perfectly well: https://3v4l.org/Gjs6D\r\n\r\nIf I use the ternary operator, like here: https://psalm.dev/r/9ac1485be3 everything is fine.\r\n\r\nI know that usage of `or` in the example is not really ideal (even if fully valid), but I used it a very simple way to demonstrate the issue.\r\n\r\nIn PHP, when there's `{condition} and {statement}`, then `statement` is executed only if `condition` is true (using `or` only if `condition` is false).\r\n\r\nThis behavior is completely unsupported in Psalm.\r\n\r\nNote how even using `&&` and `||` won't help in this case, in fact, it seems that logic operators are taken into consideration inside `if` or other statements like `while`, but now when outside any of those.","closed_by":{"login":"muglug","id":2292638,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIyOTI2Mzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2292638?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug","html_url":"https://github.com/muglug","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/muglug/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/vimeo/psalm/issues/2474/reactions","total_coun